def: A tablet; a notebook.Put into your tablebook whatever you judge worthly. Dryden.
One who, or that which, mitigates.
In the top; at the mast head, or on the higher yards orrigging; overhead; hence (Fig. and Colloq.), in or to heaven.
Expressing the same thing with different words; -- opposed toallegorical. [R.] Coleridge.
A spore borne at the extremity of the cells of fructificationin fungi.
One skilled in subjective philosophy; a subjectivist.
A lattice or grating.The grille which formed part of the gate. L. Oliphant.

To make simple; to make less complex; to make clear by givingthe explanation for; to show an easier or shorter process for doingor making.The collection of duties is drawn to a point, and so far simplified.A. Hamilton.It is important, in scientific pursuits, to be caitious insimplifying our deductions. W. Nicholson.
Having grooves or furrows broader than the intervening ridges;furrowed.
A division of shrimplike Thoracostraca in which each of thethoracic legs has a long fringed upper branch (exopodite) forswimming.
